        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 23 at 5:28PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 528 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Plymouth, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Nappanee, Bremen, Bourbon, Locke, Etna Green, La Paz, Linkville, and
Lake Of The Woods.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
